indet. (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1172,1459,1485]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="16.[132,143,778,795]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,733]" captionTargetId="figure-570@16.[132,1455,215,734]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIG. 10. — Anuran remains from Angeac-Charente:A, B, right tibiofibular of Anura indet.(ANG M-63) in anterior (A) and posterior (B) views; C, D, urostyle of Anura indet. (ANG M- 64) in dorsal (C) and ventral (D) views. Scale bar represents: A, B, 5 mm; C, D, 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902055" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902055/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="695">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
